7.Given an array nums containing n distinct numbers in the range [0, n], return the only number in the range that is missing from the array.
Platform:Leetcode
SOURCE CODE :class Solution {
    public int missingNumber(int[] nums) {
        int n=nums.length;
         int sum=0;
         int result=0;
       for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
        sum+=nums[i];
       }
       if(n>0){
        result=n*(n+1)/2 - sum;
        return result;
       }
    return 0;   }
}
