8.Given an integer array nums, return the third distinct maximum number in this array. If the third maximum does not exist, return the maximum number.
Platform:Leetcode
SOURCE CODE :class Solution {
    public int thirdMax(int[] nums) {
        TreeSet<Integer> s = new TreeSet<>();
        for(int n:nums) { s.add(n);} 
        if(s.size()<3) return s.last();
        s.pollLast();
       s.pollLast();
       return s.last(); }
}
